#### variancePartition
Estimate how much each covariate explains the variability in expression values

```{r  warning = TRUE}
# Run the variancePartition analysis on the counts table to account for contributions of each covariate to data variability:

  # First file must be the counts: genes in rows and samples in columns
  # Second must be the metadata: all covariates for each sample
  # Third must be the formula

covariates = samples
form = ~ age + (1|individual) + (1|cell_type) # + (1|RIN) 

exp_varpart <- counts(set)
varPart <- fitExtractVarPartModel(exp_varpart, form, covariates)
vp <- sortCols(varPart)
plotPercentBars(vp[1:10,])
png("/PROJECT_DIR/RSEM_quant/allsamples_variancePartition_total.png", units="in", width=8, height=4, res=800)
plotVarPart(vp)
dev.off()
plotVarPart(vp)
```

